Figure 2. Proportion of acre treatments by herbicide site of action for four crops in the US, 1990 to 2014. An acre treatment is a single application of a herbicide site of action applied to a single acre; for example a single mixture application of 2,4-D + dicamba + atrazine would equal three acre treatments (two group 4 plus one group 5).

Figure 3. Average herbicide acre treatments by site of action for four crops in the US, 1990 to 2014. An acre treatment is a single application of a herbicide site of action applied to a single acre; for example a single mixture application of 2,4-D + dicamba + atrazine would equal three acre treatments (two group 4 plus one group 5).
